President Obama delivered a speech at an event for the Illinois Coordinated Victory Fund with Congressman Tammy Duckworth in Chicago. He began by acknowledging the recent hurricane and expressing his commitment to providing support to affected states. Obama then praised Duckworth and urged the audience to support her in her campaign for Senate. He outlined Duckworth's stance on various issues, including education, veterans' rights, Social Security, and criminal justice reform. Obama contrasted Duckworth's positions with those of her opponent, emphasizing the importance of this election and the need to vote for Duckworth and Hillary Clinton. He criticized the rhetoric of the Republican presidential candidate and called for a politics of unity and respect. Obama concluded by urging the audience to work hard and get involved in the election process to ensure a better future for the country.